# Gmail to Slack Forwarder - Environment Variables Example
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values
# IMPORTANT: Never commit the actual .env file to version control!

# === REQUIRED SCRIPT PROPERTIES ===
# These 3 properties MUST be set in Google Apps Script Properties

# 1. Email address to monitor for incoming messages
SENDER_EMAIL=your-sender@example.com

# 2. Slack Incoming Webhook URL (get from your Slack workspace)
SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL=https://hooks.slack.com/services/TXXXXXXXX/BXXXXXXXX/your-webhook-key

# 3. Slack channel where notifications will be sent
SLACK_CHANNEL=your-channel

# === OPTIONAL PROPERTIES ===
# These will be auto-generated if not set

# Google Drive folder ID for storing attachments
# Leave commented for auto-creation, or set your own folder ID
# To get folder ID: https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/YOUR_FOLDER_ID
# DRIVE_FOLDER_ID=1ABC123XYZ789def456

# === SETUP INSTRUCTIONS ===
# 1. Get your Slack webhook:
#    - Go to your Slack workspace
#    - Add "Incoming Webhooks" app
#    - Select channel and copy webhook URL
#
# 2. Set in Google Apps Script:
#    Method 1: Run setRequiredConfiguration() with your values
#    Method 2: Manually add to Project Settings â†’ Script Properties
#
# 3. Values to set:
#    Key: SENDER_EMAIL        Value: your-sender@example.com
#    Key: SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL   Value: https://hooks.slack.com/services/TXXXXXXXX/BXXXXXXXX/your-webhook-key
#    Key: SLACK_CHANNEL       Value: your-channel (or #your-channel)
#    Key: DRIVE_FOLDER_ID     Value: 1ABC123XYZ789def456 (optional - leave blank for auto-creation)